Place this pi_arduino_bridge package onto the pi in the ros2_ws/src workspace 
To run, paste these commands step by step into the terminal: 
cd rps2_ws
source install/setup.bash
ros2 run pi_arduino_bridge bridge

Enter a new terminal
#to see list of active topics 
ros2 topic list
#to see live IMU data
ros2 topic echo /imu_data
#to see wheel speeds
ros2 topic echo /left_encoder_data
ros2 topic echo /right_encoder_data

Diagnostic Commands. If you don't see data appearing, use these commands to troubleshoot:

#Check Frequency: See if the data is actually coming in at the 50Hz (20ms) rate you set in your timer.
ros2 topic hz /imu_data
#Check Topic Info: See which nodes are publishing and which are subscribing.
ros2 topic info /imu_data --verbose
#Check Active Nodes: Confirm your node name appears on the graph.
ros2 node list
